<Base
  title="About — Jeff Mills"
  description="Principal-level front-end engineer with 20+ years building enterprise web platforms, design systems, and AI-integrated product experiences."
>
  <h1 class="page-title">about</h1>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <div class="about-prose">
    <p>
      I&rsquo;m Jeff, a Principal-level Front-End Engineer with 20+ years
      across fast-moving Philadelphia agencies and Vanguard. I architected
      the framework-agnostic design system (AXS) that powers 11 product
      teams and the firm&rsquo;s main advisor portal, and I lead the
      engineering teams behind AXS and Expert Insights &mdash;
      Vanguard&rsquo;s AI-driven portfolio analysis platform that reached
      110,000 financial advisors on launch in April 2026.
    </p>

    <p>
      The agency years taught me speed; Vanguard taught me scale. The
      instincts compose. What I&rsquo;m drawn to: durable abstractions, the
      design decisions that age well across platform shifts you didn&rsquo;t
      see coming. The Vue-to-Web-Components approach I built years ago quietly
      became the foundation for generative-UI work nobody had imagined yet.
    </p>

    <p>
      I work player-coach style: I write code alongside the engineers I lead,
      pair-program through the hard parts, and stay close to the production
      codebase. Lately that means a lot of AI-assisted coding with Claude,
      including a two-month team refactor from Vue to Lit and a Gen UI
      prototype I built solo 
    </p>

    <p class="about-locale">
      <span class="jm-badge">&gt;</span>Based in the Philadelphia area.
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <p class="about-cta">
    Open to Principal Front-End roles. <a href="mailto:jeffy9@gmail.com">say hello</a>
    &middot; <a href="/resume">read resume</a>
    &middot; <a href="https://github.com/k0bura">github.com/k0bura</a>
  </p>
</Base>

